🔥 Firebase Setup Guide – E-Commerce Web App
This guide explains how to set up Firebase Authentication, Firestore Database, and Firebase Hosting for your E-Commerce project.

✅ Step 1: Create a Firebase Project
Go to 👉 https://console.firebase.google.com

Click “Add Project”

Project Name: E-Commerce

Disable Google Analytics (optional)

Click Create Project

✅ Step 2: Add a Web App
Inside your Firebase project, click the Web (</>) icon

App nickname: ecommerce-web

Click Register App

Copy the config snippet and paste it in:

📄 public/scripts/firebase-config.js

// firebase-config.js
import { initializeApp } from "https://www.gstatic.com/firebasejs/10.11.0/firebase-app.js";

const firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
  authDomain: "your-app.firebaseapp.com",
  projectId: "your-app",
  storageBucket: "your-app.appspot.com",
  messagingSenderId: "YOUR_SENDER_ID",
  appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};

export const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);
✅ Step 3: Enable Authentication
Go to Build → Authentication

Click Get Started

Under Sign-in Method, enable:

✅ Email/Password

✅ Step 4: Enable Firestore Database
Go to Build → Firestore Database

Click Create Database

Choose Start in test mode for development

Select your preferred region (e.g., asia-south1)

Click Enable

✅ Step 5: Firestore Collections Structure
🛒 Collection: orders
Each document represents a single order placed by a user.

Example structure:

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "cart": [
    {
      "productId": "p001",
      "title": "Red Shoes",
      "price": 899,
      "quantity": 2
    },
    {
      "productId": "p002",
      "title": "T-Shirt",
      "price": 499,
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "address": "Hyderabad, India",
  "paymentMethod": "UPI",
  "total": 2297,
  "timestamp": "2025-08-03T18:23:00Z"
}
✅ Step 6: Install Firebase CLI
Make sure you have Node.js installed

Install Firebase CLI:

npm install -g firebase-tools
✅ Step 7: Login to Firebase
Login to Firebase CLI:

firebase login
✅ Step 8: Initialize Firebase in Your Project
Go to your project folder:

cd path/to/E-Commerce
Then initialize Firebase:

firebase init
Select the following:
✅ Hosting

✅ Firestore

✅ Authentication

Set public directory as: public

Configure as SPA? → Yes
Overwrite index.html? → No

📁 Final Project Structure
E-Commerce/
├── .firebaserc                 ✅ Firebase project ID
├── firebase.json               ✅ Hosting config
├── public/
│   ├── index.html              🏠 Homepage
│   ├── register.html           📝 User registration
│   ├── login.html              🔐 Login page
│   ├── home.html               🛍️ Product listings           
│   ├── cart.html               🛒 Cart page
│   ├── address.html            📍 Address input/payment page        
│   ├── success.html            ✅ Order confirmation
│   ├── css/
│   └── scripts/
├── README.md                   📘 Project explanation
├── FIREBASE_SETUP.md           🔥 This guide


🛠️ Commands to Run in CMD
cd path/to/E-Commerce
firebase login
firebase init
firebase deploy

🌐 After Deployment
Firebase will give you a URL like:

✔ Hosting URL: https://ecommerce-yaswanth.web.app
You can now access your live e-commerce website online.

